Junior Software Developer – Entry Level

Evan Leigh Real Estate

- Boca Raton, FL 33487

How would like the opportunity to work on a brand new software system in the real estate industry? We are looking for a junior software developer to help kick-off our latest project. This is a new code base, that means greenfield development, new opportunities to learn and best of all, no legacy code. You’ll have the opportunity to learn and work on the latest technology while applying the best software development practices. Our development space in agile and collaborative. We support and encourage continuous training with company provided educational resources and mentoring.
Job Requirements:
Design, write, comment, and test new software based on architectural diagrams and user stories.
Design and implement data models and object structures.
Document processes and systems for technical and non-technical staff.
Identify and correct code defects effectively.
Actively participate in daily scrum meetings.
Regular collaboration with technical and business staff.
Adherence to coding standards and departmental procedures.
Reliable and punctual attendance.
The Tech stack:
C#, JavaScript, SQL, HTML, jQuery, Bootstrap
.Net Core 3 - Web API and Razor Pages
DevOps (git)
REST APIs w/JSON
100% cloud infrastructure hosted on Azure/Docker
Microservices Architecture and Event Sourcing
Test Driven Development
Continuous Integration/Continuous Delivery
Dependency Injection and Inversion of Control
What we are looking for:
2 to 4 years of education working on a mainstream object-oriented language. For example: C#, Java, or Python.
2 to 4 years of education working on mainstream database systems (SQL Server, PostgreSQL, MySQL, NoSQL).
Solid understand of the HTTP Request/Response model.
Self-starter with the drive and motivation to learn.
Solid work ethic to deliver effective solutions.
Willingness to work in all aspects of the SDLC.
Excellent communications skills.
Nice-to-haves but not required:
Bachelor’s degree in computer science or equivalent work experience.
Experience working on Microsoft technology stack particularly .Net Core.
Web Design Experience (CSS/Bootstrap/styling and graphics)
Experience with asynchronous development methodology.
Benefits:
Generous paid time off policy, 401k retirement plan with company matching, health benefits, casual work environment, fully stocked break room, monthly company luncheon and much more.
Compensation will be based on experience and skill level.
Job Type: Full-time
